# Declared runtime dependencies for the in-Wine MCP server (Windows Python 3.12).
# This is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for what the image installs. The pinned lockfile
# (requirements.txt) MUST be generated from the actual amd64 Wine build to satisfy
# the constitution's "pinned, reproducible" rule:
#
#   # inside the built image, in the Wine Python:
#   wine python -m pip install -r requirements.in
#   wine python -m pip freeze > requirements.txt
#
# then change the Dockerfile from the unpinned
#   pip install fastmcp uvicorn numpy pandas
# to
#   pip install -r requirements.txt
# and rebuild + smoke-test on amd64.
#
# (Pinning cannot be verified from a non-amd64 host, so the lock is intentionally
# not committed by automation — generate it on a real build. See 011 spec FR-006.)

fastmcp
uvicorn
numpy
pandas
